-- Oil Rises First Time in Three Days as Crude Supply Drop Exceeds Forecasts
-- B y   J o s e p h   L i n k
-- 2010-12-09T18:12:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-09/crude-oil-rises-after-hovensa-refinery-unit-shut-for-unplanned-maintenance.html
Crude oil rose after Hovensa LLC said
it shut a fluid catalytic cracker at its refinery in the U.S.
Virgin Islands for repairs.  Crude oil for January delivery climbed 74 cents, or 0.8
percent, to $89.02 a barrel at 1:10 p.m. on the New York
Mercantile Exchange. Oil earlier fell as low as $87.71.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joseph Link at 
 jlink1@bloomberg.net  